Use `fromEvent` on the input, filter to Enter, map to a typed draft, then push into a Subject the rest of the pipeline consumes.

```typescript
import { fromEvent, Subject, Observable, filter, map } from "rxjs";

interface DraftMessage { id: string; body: string; }

export function wireInput(el: HTMLInputElement): Observable<DraftMessage> {
  const out$ = new Subject<DraftMessage>();
  fromEvent<KeyboardEvent>(el, "keydown")
    .pipe(
      filter((ev: KeyboardEvent) => ev.key === "Enter" && el.value.trim().length > 0),
      map((): DraftMessage => ({ id: crypto.randomUUID(), body: el.value.trim() }))
    )
    .subscribe((d: DraftMessage) => out$.next(d));
  return out$.asObservable();
}
```

Optimistic UI emits a synthetic `pending` event immediately when the user sends, so the message appears in the list before the server confirms. The server response then upgrades the row to `ack` (or downgrades to `error`). In RxJS, `merge(of(pending), send$)` inside `mergeMap` gives you both emissions from a single source event, keyed by message id.

```typescript
