Pass an object to `combineLatest` and `map` the merged value into your ViewModel type. combineLatest fires once every input has emitted at least one value and re-fires whenever any input emits.

```typescript
import { Observable, BehaviorSubject, combineLatest, map } from "rxjs";

interface ViewModel { latencyMs: number; errorRate: number; status: "ok" | "warn" | "bad"; }

const latency$ = new BehaviorSubject<number>(120);
const errors$ = new BehaviorSubject<number>(0.01);

export const vm$: Observable<ViewModel> = combineLatest({
  latencyMs: latency$,
  errorRate: errors$
}).pipe(
  map(({ latencyMs, errorRate }): ViewModel => ({
    latencyMs,
    errorRate,
    status: errorRate > 0.05 ? "bad" : latencyMs > 500 ? "warn" : "ok"
  }))
);
```

`combineLatest` does not emit until every input source has emitted at least once. That means if any metric is a cold Observable or is slow to produce its first value, the dashboard stays empty. Using `BehaviorSubject` with seed values guarantees each source emits immediately on subscribe, so the ViewModel fires on the first tick.

