Cross-field validation means a rule whose truth depends on more than one field (e.g. passwordConfirm must equal password). You expose each field as its own Observable (usually a BehaviorSubject seeded with the empty value), `combineLatest` them, and `map` to a ViewModel containing per-field and whole-form validity. Every field emission re-runs the derivation, so the form is always consistent.

